  "text": "To determine whether the tomato CRTR-B enzymes could add hydroxyl groups also to e-ring carotenoids, we cotransfected pCrtR-b1 or pCrtR-b2 to a d-carotene accumulating E. coli cells that carried the plasmid pDCAR [CITATION_1] . No alteration in carotenoid composition was observed in these cells, indicating that both CRTR-B enzymes in tomato were incapable of hydroxylation of e-ring in d-carotene in E. coli cells ( Table 2) .",
